  "notes": "Madurese (Bhâsa Madhurâ) in the Latin orthography (Alfabet Latèn); a Javanese-script orthography also exists and is not covered here. Distinctive three-way laryngeal contrast in stops — voiceless unaspirated, voiced, and a breathy/aspirated series written with ⟨h⟩ digraphs (bh, dh, jh, gh). Nine vowels; the Latin norm writes /ɛ/ as ⟨è⟩ and /ɤ/ as ⟨â⟩, while plain ⟨e⟩ covers /ə/ and /ɨ/, so ⟨e⟩ is genuinely ambiguous. Retroflex ṭ/ḍ and the retroflex nasal are dialectal/typographic variants not represented in the base map.",
